<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
A common species on alkaline habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Hils, MH" editor="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, eds." journalOrPublisher="New York and Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Flora of North America North of Mexico" year="1993">Hils et al. 1993</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sarcobataceae" genus="Sarcobatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcobatus vermiculatus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">Sarcobatus vermiculatus</taxonomicName>
was found in greatest abundance along the banks of a seasonally wet stream crossing due northeast of MDRS (Fig. 46). Previously placed within the 
<taxonomicName family="Chenopodiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sarcobataceae" genus="Sarcobatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcobatus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Sarcobatus</taxonomicName>
is now recognized as the sole genus within the 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcobataceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="family">Sarcobataceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Behnke, H-D" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="495 - 507" title="Sarcobataceae - a new family of Caryophyllales" volume="46" year="1997">Behnke 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="APG III," journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="105 - 121" title="An update of the Angiosperm Phylogeny Group classification for the orders and families of flowering plants: APG III" volume="161" year="2009">APG III 2009</bibRefCitation>
). This species was previously recorded for the nearby San Rafael Swell (
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
